1
00:00:00,334 --> 00:00:03,709
They brought us from the prefabricated room

2
00:00:04,125 --> 00:00:07,626
In the prefabricated room they took the personal belongings

3
00:00:07,918 --> 00:00:13,375
Then they blindfolded us and made us go up
these stairs until we reached this room

4
00:00:13,959 --> 00:00:15,751
There were prisoners in it

5
00:00:16,417 --> 00:00:18,918
Because of smoking, the <i>izar</i> [waist wrap], and other matters

6
00:00:18,959 --> 00:00:21,584
We couldn’t ask them about that because we didn’t know them

7
00:00:21,959 --> 00:00:25,250
If you don’t know someone well, you can’t ask him

8
00:00:25,709 --> 00:00:27,792
This is the room we stayed in

9
00:00:28,459 --> 00:00:32,834
And we slept in it, here were the sinks and toilets

10
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,542
And there were prisoners

11
00:00:36,876 --> 00:00:40,751
Many of them were accused of smoking

12
00:00:40,959 --> 00:00:44,375
Or of another matter, or they were policemen

13
00:00:44,375 --> 00:00:47,250
Or we didn’t know what their charge was

14
00:00:47,334 --> 00:00:51,918
They would bring people in and take others out
We feared one of them might be an informant for them

15
00:00:51,959 --> 00:00:55,918
And that he would lure us into talking, these people were not good

16
00:00:55,959 --> 00:00:59,459
We didn’t know our fate so we were afraid of each other

17
00:01:00,542 --> 00:01:06,083
They would take people and bring them down to the basement

18
00:01:06,417 --> 00:01:12,292
We didn’t dare ask what they were questioned about, or what they’d said to the judge

19
00:01:12,959 --> 00:01:15,792
Here is where people slept, and here were the mattresses

20
00:01:16,584 --> 00:01:19,667
And these are the toilets

21
00:01:20,209 --> 00:01:23,584
These toilets were separate

22
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:26,959
They were outside the room, but they made this opening in them
